'''Loci Rosen''' was a [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]]<ref name="Episode VI" /> [[Gender/Legends|male]].<ref name="Topps" /> He was formerly a [[Merchant/Legends|merchant]] while looking for work, although everywhere he went, he turned up empty [[Limb/Legends|handed]].<ref name="CCG" /> Rosen served the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] as a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]]<ref name="FF 20">{{FactFile|20|PIL 1-4|Training Rebel Alliance Pilots}}</ref> during the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|III|110|Rosen, Loci}}</ref> in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> where he served as an [[Officer/Legends|officer]].<ref name="CSWE" /> At the battle, the Alliance successfully destroyed the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]]. Following the battle, Rosen was among the many to dance while celebrating the victory on the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]],<ref name="Episode VI" /> playing a [[Music/Legends|musical]] instrument while doing so.<ref name="ROTJ 4">[[Return of the Jedi 4|''Return of the Jedi'' 4]]</ref> He also served as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]].<ref name="Intro">''[[Introductory Adventure Game]]''</ref>

Rosen wore a [[Mon Calamari helmet|helmet]]<ref name="Episode VI" /> that signified a high rank in the Rebel Alliance, offered moderate protection, and had a built-in [[Comm unit/Legends|communication device]].<ref name="Hasbro">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: Power of the Jedi|pack=Mon Calamari Officer|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/potjmoncalamari.asp}}</ref> He also donned a [[Color/Legends|beige]]<ref name="Episode VI" /> [[Mon Calamari Crewman uniform]].<ref name="WEG">[[The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref> Rosen was good-willed even as his search for work was unsuccessful. He had brown-mottled skin and orange [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="CCG" /> His first name meant "ingenious," while Rosen was a female name translating to "pure."<ref name="GCG">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Loci Rosen was created for the [[1983]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="Episode VI" /> During production he was referred to as "Forest Ackbar."<ref name="Much">{{SW|url=news/much-to-learn-you-still-have-10-things-you-might-not-know-about-mon-calamari|text=Much to Learn You Still Have: 10 Things You Might Not Know About Mon Calamari}}</ref> The scenes in which he appeared were filmed between [[January 20]] and [[January 22|22]] of [[1982]] on Stage 3 in [[Wikipedia:Crescent City, California|Crescent City]], [[Wikipedia:California|California]]. [[:File:LociConcept.jpg|Conceptual art]] that was originally intended to be of [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]] was repurposed to become Rosen, or as it was labeled, "Forest Akbar." The art, done by [[Nilo Rodis-Jamero]], was accompanied by instructions and Polaroids on how to wear the character's costume.<ref name="making">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref>

Rosen was first identified on a card for the [[2001]] ''[[Tatooine Limited]]'' expansion for the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" /> The [[1995]] reference book ''[[The Essential Guide to Characters]]'', [[Panini]]'s [[1997]] [[Star Wars: Collectible Sticker and Story Album|sticker album]], the [[1998]] reference book ''[[Star Wars Who's Who: A Pocket Guide to the Characters of the Star Wars Trilogy]]'', and the [[1999]] [[Star Wars Kids (1997) 19|nineteenth issue]] of the [[Star Wars Kids (1997)|''Star Wars Kids'']] magazine all mistakenly use an image of Rosen to depict Admiral Gial Ackbar.<ref name="egtc">''[[The Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref><ref name="Panini">[[Star Wars: Collectible Sticker and Story Album|''Star Wars'': Collectible Sticker and Story Album]]</ref><ref name="who">''[[Star Wars Who's Who: A Pocket Guide to the Characters of the Star Wars Trilogy]]''</ref><ref name="SWK19">[[Star Wars Kids (1997) 19|''Star Wars Kids'' (1997) 19]]</ref>

